    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but if you look at the actual data from the last few years, doesn't the evidence show that these benefits are a primary driver in people staying out of the workforce? like, isn't it pretty clear that there's a direct correlation between increased benefits and lower participation?",
